Film star Kate Henshaw recently joined Nigerian businesswoman Ibukun Awosika to speak at the annual mega-conference,  SheCan Nigeria. Henshaw and Awosika joined other speakers at the fourth edition of the conference which was held at the Harbour Point on Victoria Island, Lagos. The event, which also featured a number of industry leaders both men and women who spoke, taught, mentored, and advised the women was thrown open by the founder, SheCan Nigeria, Ezinne Ezeani.   I’ll not let you down, Adeleke tells Timi of Ede     Lagos steps down new abortion guidelines     Kuje attack: Senate shocked by no CCTV, porous security   Other speakers included Funke Felix Adejumo, Oyeyimika Adeboye, Tara Fela Durotoye, and Lanre “The Catalyst” Olusola, Junadia Edim, Olusegun Adeniyi, and Belinda Ikazoboh. The SheCan Nigeria conference seeks to impact, empower and mentor women and girls all over Nigeria and beyond. Mentoring sessions were held for attendees as Ezeani promised that other events slated for the year aimed at empowering women to do more are still going to hold including the SheCan Skill Acquisition program scheduled to hold from the 25th to the 30th of July in Lagos.  “The programme would feature career fairs and vocational training for girls at the girls’ correctional center as well as a SheCan Nigeria enterprise program. As part of the conference sustainability plan, several mentorship and roundtable sessions have also been scheduled,” she revealed. The SheCanDoMore conference has become one of the biggest convergence of today’s women in Nigeria.